  "notes": "Paths relative to template root. Use glob patterns. User-created rule files (project-*.md) and reference docs (project-*.md) are ignored by sync. The settings file is layered: `.claude/settings.json` is template-owned (in `sync`) and contains only the base `permissions.allow`; `.claude/settings.local.json` is user-owned (in `ignore`) and holds user additions, hooks, env vars, and theme. Claude Code merges both layers at runtime."
